description:
Ghost World is a graphic novel written and illustrated by Daniel Clowes. It was originally serialized in issues #11 through 18 (June 1993 to March 1997) of Clowes&amp;#039;s comic book series Eightball,[1] and was first published in book form in 1997 by Fantagraphics Books. A commercial and critical success, it was very popular with teenage audiences on its initial release and developed into a cult classic. The book has been reprinted in multiple editions[2] and was the basis for the 2001 feature film of the same name.
